%I A395182 #15 Apr 20 2026 23:51:27
%S A395182 3,29928,100488,259080,502680,597528,619368,896808,1708248,2093808,
%T A395182 2493240,2601768,2647128,3485688,4798248,5508408,6086088,7252248
%N A395182 Numbers in A395181 which are not totient numbers.
%C A395182 Under a multiplication which is not completely multiplicative, for a quadratic number ring which is a UFD, the full set of values of its Euler totient function can be produced from the set {(p-1)*p^(e-1), (q^2-1)*(q^2)^(e-1)} for all primes p and q where p is either ramified or split, and q is inert. For the totient values in Z (A002202), the initial set is {(p-1)p^(e-1)} for all primes p. The totient values of a quadratic UFD may omit totient values of Z but it may also contain totient values which are not totient values of Z. The present sequence lists those additional values.
%e A395182 3 is a term since (2^2-1)*(2^2)^0 = 3 and 3 is not in A002202.
%e A395182 29928 is a term since (173^2)*(173^2)^0 = 29928 and 29928 is not in A002202.
%e A395182 4798248 is a term since (13^2-1)*(13^2)^2 = 4798248 and 4798248 is not in A002202.
%o A395182 (PARI) lst(lim) = my(S = Set([1])); forprime(p = 2, lim, my(L = List()); for(e = 1, oo, my(v = (p^2)^(e-1) * (p^2 - 1)); if(istotient(v) || v > lim, break); listput(L, v)); my(T = Set(S)); for(i = 1, #S, for(j = 1, #L, my(v = S[i] * L[j]); if(istotient(v), next); if(v <= lim, T = setunion(T, Set([v]))))); S = T); setminus(S, [1])
%Y A395182 Cf. A002202, A395181.
%K A395182 nonn,more,new
%O A395182 1,1
%A A395182 _Miles Englezou_, Apr 15 2026
